@startuml developer-onboarding
title Developer Onboarding — Register Vault + Run Middleware (Arc Testnet)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #FFF3E0
skinparam participantBorderColor #FF9800

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "Circle Faucet\n(faucet.circle.com)" as Faucet
participant "register CLI\n(scripts/register.ts)" as CLI
participant "PaymentSplitterFactory\n(Arc Testnet)" as Factory
participant "Developer's Vault\n(EIP-1167 clone,\nat deterministic addr)" as Vault
participant "Developer Service\n(withPaywall middleware)" as Service

== Step 1: Get test USDC ==
Dev -> Faucet : Request 1 USDC on Arc Testnet
Faucet -> Dev : USDC arrives at developer EOA\n(also pays Arc gas — USDC is native gas token)

== Step 2: Register (deploys vault) ==
Dev -> CLI : npx universal-paywall register \\\n  --network arc-testnet
note over CLI : REGISTER_KEY env holds\nthe developer's private key
CLI -> Factory : register()\n(from developer EOA)
Factory -> Factory : require !paused, !already registered
Factory -> Vault : Clones.cloneDeterministic(\n   vaultImpl,\n   bytes32(uint256(uint160(msg.sender))))
Vault -> Vault : initialize(developer = msg.sender)\nfactory = msg.sender(=Factory)
Factory -> Factory : vaults[msg.sender] = vault\nemit VaultDeployed
Factory --> CLI : (tx hash, vault address)
CLI -> Dev : ✅ Registered\nvault: 0xDevVault...\narcscan: https://testnet.arcscan.app/address/0xDevVault...

== Step 3: Install + configure middleware ==
Dev -> Service : npm install @universal-paywall/middleware

Dev -> Service : Server code:\n\nimport { withPaywall } from\n  '@universal-paywall/middleware';\n\nconst server = http.createServer(\n  withPaywall(myHandler, {\n    price: '0.01',\n    developerEoa: '0xDev...',\n    network: 'arc-testnet',\n    facilitator: {\n      mode: 'inline',\n      relayerKey: process.env.PAYWALL_RELAYER_KEY\n    }\n  })\n);

note over Service
  Factory + vault addresses baked into
  middleware NETWORKS map.
  Vault address is computed deterministically
  (no RPC needed for 402).
  Relayer key funds Arc gas — needs USDC.
end note

== Step 4: Balance check & withdrawal ==

Dev -> Vault : (off-chain read)\nUSDC.balanceOf(vaultAddress)
Vault -> Dev : balance (micro-USDC)

Dev -> Vault : withdraw()  (signed from dev EOA)
Vault -> Vault : require msg.sender == developer\ngross = USDC.balanceOf(this)\nrequire gross > 0\nfee = gross * factory.feeBps() / 10000\nnet = gross - fee
Vault -> Dev : USDC.safeTransfer(developer, net)
Vault -> "Platform Treasury" : USDC.safeTransfer(treasury, fee)\n(if fee > 0)
Vault -> Vault : emit Withdrawal(developer, gross, fee)

@enduml
